Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and deseed the @Bell Pepper{1%unit}. Slice into thin strips.

Halve the @Cherry Tomatoes{125%grams}.

Peel and grate the @Garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #bowl{}, mix the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%grams} with a drizzle of @Oil{to taste}, half the @Honey{1%sachet} and half the garlic. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Lay the chicken out on a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with more oil and season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Garlic Rice ==

Meanwhile, place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with @Butter{1%tbsp} (per 2P).

Once hot, add the remaining garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Rice{150%grams} and stir until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock{1%sachet} and @Water{300%ml} (per 2P). Bring to the boil. Once boiling, lower heat to medium and cover.

Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat. Leave aside for ~{10%minutes} (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Roasted Peppers and Cherry Tomatoes ==

When the chicken has been roasting for ~{5-10%minutes}, remove the tray from the oven.

Place the bell pepper and cherry tomatoes alongside the chicken on the tray.

Drizzle with oil and the remaining @Honey{1%sachet}. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Return to the top shelf to cook for the remaining time, ~{15-18%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

When the chicken and veg are cooked, remove the tray from the oven.

Add half the @Green Pesto{30%grams} to the roasted veg and toss to coat evenly.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Slice the chicken breasts widthways into 1cm thick slices.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between #bowls{}.

Top with the pesto chicken and veg, spooning over all the juices from the tray.

Spoon the remaining pesto over the chicken to finish.